Brazilian Stock Movers: BRF Brasil Foods, Redecard SA, Usiminas

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-02-18T20:54:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/brazilian-stock-movers-brf-brasil-foods-redecard-sa-usiminas.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index rose 0.6 percent to 68,066.82.  BRF Brasil Foods SA (BRFS3 BS) jumped 3.3 percent to 29.65
reais. Valor Economico newspaper reported that billionaire
investor  Warren Buffett ’s Berkshire Hathaway Inc. started buying
shares in the Brazilian company, the world’s biggest poultry
exporter.    Redecard SA  (RDCD3 BS) advanced 2.5 percent to 21.08 reais.
Brazil’s second-biggest card-payment processor said it named
Claudio Takashi Yamaguti as chief executive officer, replacing
Roberto Medeiros, who will leave the post April 15.  Usinas Siderurgicas de Minas Gerais SA’s voting stock
(USIM3 BS) fell 1.3 percent to 26.47 reais. Usiminas, as the
steelmaker is known, said in a statement that its main
shareholders plan to retain control until at least 2031,
following speculation that rival Cia. Siderurgica Nacional may
seek to boost its stake.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in  Sao Paulo  at 
 ncruz4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
